# ImageGenDemoSystem

## Purpose
SandboxApp text-to-image demo driving a 3-step pipeline (ADR 0011). Returns early until the engine
diffusion singletons (backend + job) and the resource map exist, then lazily creates its state
singleton. Each frame it advances the running pipeline based on Diffusion Job completion and resource
availability; an ImGui "Image Generation" panel exposes the editable background style prompt + a
consistency slider + a Generate button (the G key is the same trigger, and the headless-test entry
point since the panel needs no-context guarding). A Generate trigger, when the backend is loaded and the
pipeline is idle/done, starts the sequence:

1. **Background** — emits a GenerateImageRequest into `k_BackgroundTextureID`: img2img on the original
   photo (`k_LivingRoomImageID`) with the panel's style prompt and a denoise derived from the
   consistency slider (no LoRA, no ControlNet), restyling it while preserving structure.
2. **Pose hint** — when the background job finishes, emits a RasterizeOpenPoseHintRequest into
   `k_HintTextureID` to show the OpenPose skeleton.
3. **Composite** — once the restyled background is retained as an input image (engine feed-forward),
   emits a GenerateImageRequest into `k_CompositeTextureID`: the figure is generated with txt2img +
   OpenPose ControlNet (`k_DiffusionSkeletonID`) + the SDXL character LoRA (`k_DiffusionLoraID`, weight 0.8,
   with its trigger word `ff7t1f4` leading the prompt) on a plain background, then composited onto the
   restyled background (`m_BackgroundImageID = k_BackgroundTextureID`) through the figure's per-pixel Alpha
   Matte (`m_CompositeWithMatte`), which cuts the character out by its real outline and so removes the
   skeleton silhouette's "gray cloud" halo (ADR 0012). When the matting backend is unavailable the composite
   falls back to the skeleton silhouette (the `Composite mask tightness` knob tunes only that fallback).
   img2img is not used — img2img + ControlNet NaNs the latent to flat grey on this checkpoint (ADR 0011);
   the composite is a CPU blend that always renders. The LoRA must be the same architecture as the resident
   checkpoint (an Illustrious/SDXL LoRA for this SDXL checkpoint); a wrong-architecture LoRA binds 0 tensors
   and is silently ignored. When that job finishes the pipeline is done.

Each generation step waits for its Diffusion Job (seen running, then idle); only one job runs at a time,
so the engine serialises the steps. The three result UUIDs are shown side by side by SceneSetupSystem.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| KeyPressedEventComponent | read | G key starts the pipeline (also the headless-test trigger) |
| DiffusionBackendSingletonComponent | read | Readiness gate: only start once the checkpoint is loaded |
| DiffusionJobSingletonComponent | read | Active-job state drives the per-step completion detection |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read | The restyled background appearing as an input image gates the composite step |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| ImageGenDemoStateSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once; holds the panel state (prompt, consistency) + pipeline step + job-seen flag |
| GenerateImageRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | The background and composite generation requests (engine-typed), read by the engine DiffusionSystem |
| RasterizeOpenPoseHintRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | The pose-hint rasterization request (engine-typed), read by the engine DiffusionSystem |
